chatSpace.how_can_i_help_you_today: How can I help you today?
chatSpace.system_prompt_description: You can use system prompts to describe the personality of your assistant, define what the model should and should not respond to, and define the format of the model's response.
chatSpace.auto_run_workflow_description: When the AI determines that it needs to run a workflow to complete the task, it will automatically run the workflow and return the result.
chatSpace.cant_open_template_record: Can't open workflow template record page
chatSpace.share_chat_description: Messages sent after creating the link will not be shared. Anyone with the link can view the shared chat. The workflow run records involved in the chat will be set to the shared state.
chatSpace.message_changed_after_last_share: The chat message has been added since the last share, closing and reopening the share will update.
chatSpace.input_too_large: The input content is too long, please shorten it and try again.
chatSpace.share_to_community_brief: After sharing publicly to the community, other users can see the chat record in the share list. Otherwise, it can only be accessed through the share link.
chatSpace.workflow_title_clickable: Click the title to expand the workflow run record details
chatSpace.agent_audio_reply_description: Play the agent's reply with audio after the agent generates the reply
chatSpace.native_multimodal_description: If the model supports multimodal, uploaded images will be passed directly to the model.

agentSpace.no_agents_1: You haven't created any AI agent yet
agentSpace.no_agents_2: You can view official AI agent or create a new AI agent
agentSpace.agent_name_placeholder: Please enter the name of the AI agent
agentSpace.agent_description_placeholder: Please enter the function introduction of the agent.
agentSpace.delete_agent_confirm_content: {name} will be deleted, and the chat record will be deleted.
agentSpace.add_templates_to_your_workflows: Do you want to add the workflow templates in this Agent as your personal workflows? After adding, you can review the workflow run records. If not added, this Agent will not be associated with any workflows and will require manual handling by you.
agentSpace.system_prompt_tip: System prompts are special messages used to guide AI behavior, which allow developers to define the style and tasks of artificial intelligence within a certain range, making it more customizable and adaptable to various use cases.  You can use {'{{'}time{'}}'} as a time variable to tell the Agent the current time.
agentSpace.opening_question_suggestions_tip: Give a few optional opening questions so that users can start the conversation quickly.
agentSpace.toggle_agent_shared_true_content: After sharing, other users can use the agent through the link.
agentSpace.toggle_agent_shared_false_content: After canceling the sharing, other users will not be able to use the agent through the link.
agentSpace.toggle_agent_is_public_true_content: After making it public, other users can find the agent on the community public page.
agentSpace.toggle_agent_is_public_false_content: After canceling the public, other users will not be able to find the agent on the community public page.
agentSpace.workflow_become_template_warning: Your personal workflow will be automatically converted to a workflow template for other users to use.
agentSpace.database_access_control_warning: If the workflow used by your Agent involves knowledge base search, please pay attention to confirm the permission of the database. If the database is private, after converting to a workflow template, the user needs to create the database by himself. If you want users to use the database you have created directly, pay attention to change the database permission to public read.
agentSpace.model_select_tip: You can choose different AI models as the default model according to your needs. You can manually change the model during the chat.
agentSpace.cant_open_template_record: Can't open workflow template record page

workflowSpace.add_to_fast_access_confirm: Confirm to add the workflow to fast access?
workflowSpace.delete_from_fast_access_confirm: Confirm to delete the workflow from fast access?
workflowSpace.delete_schedule_trigger_confirm: Confirm to delete the schedule trigger?
workflowSpace.diagnosis_workflow_record_tip: You can now diagnose a specific workflow run record to view the running status, running time of each node.
workflowSpace.api_key_is_empty: The API Key of model {model} is not set!
workflowSpace.run_workflow_version_inconsistent_tip1: The current workflow version is inconsistent with the run record version, please select one of the following options to continue running
workflowSpace.run_workflow_version_inconsistent_tip2: If you choose to run the version from the run record, it will use the workflow structure corresponding to that record, rather than the current latest workflow structure. If you use the current latest version of the workflow structure, due to possible differences in fields, it may not be able to automatically fill and run successfully.
workflowSpace.record_version: Workflow run record corresponding to workflow version

workflowEditor.workflow_has_no_inputs: Workflow has no inputs (please check the fields you want to display in the use interface)
workflowEditor.workflow_has_no_outputs: Workflow has no outputs (please drag a node from the output to the canvas and connect it)
workflowEditor.workflow_has_no_triggers: Workflow has no triggers (please drag a node from the triggers to the canvas and connect it)
workflowEditor.workflow_has_cycles: The workflow connection has a cycle, please make sure that the connection of each node will not form a cycle
workflowEditor.workflow_has_isolated_nodes: There are isolated nodes in the workflow, please make sure that all nodes except the trigger node are connected to other nodes
workflowEditor.edge_delete_message: Press the backspace key on the keyboard or double-click the line to delete
workflowEditor.edge_already_connected_message: The handle has already connected an edge
workflowEditor.resume_node_but_edge_already_connected_m: The other end of the line has other lines, please delete other lines or ignore the nodes corresponding to the lines.

workflowSpaceMain.input_search_text: Enter the title, brief, etc. to be searched
workflowSpaceMain.no_workflows_1: You have not added or created a workflow yet

workflowTemplate.author: Author: {author}
workflowTemplate.test_run_template_hint1: It is recommended that you add it to your own workflow before running, so that you can save the record and make custom modifications.

dataSpace.delete_confirm: Confirm to delete the database? It cannot be restored after deletion!
dataSpace.vector_database_description: Vector database is a database based on vector retrieval, which can be used to store and retrieve text, images, audio, video and other data.
dataSpace.relational_database_description: Relational database is a database based on the relational model, which can be used to store and retrieve structured data.
dataSpace.embedding_provider_azure_tip: If the OpenAI type in the settings is Azure, the deployment name of Azure Embedding in the settings is used.
dataSpace.embedding_provider_text_embeddings_infer: text-embeddings-inference needs to be deployed by yourself, see details

databaseDetail.please_enter_sql: Please enter SQL statement conforming to SQLite syntax
databaseDetail.failed_to_load_database: Failed to load the database, the database may be too large or the file is damaged
databaseDetail.max_show_rows: Up to 1000 rows of data can be displayed on the page

chunk_length.1: The chunk length means that the text is divided into segments according to how long it is, for example, 1000 means that every 1000 characters are divided into one segment.
chunk_length.2: The vector database will find the most relevant paragraph and return it when searching.
chunk_length.3: Note that the paragraph length here is not strictly followed, but is roughly close.

databaseTableCreate.sql_statement_too_long: SQL statement is too long, please use the file upload method to upload the SQL file.
databaseTableCreate.upload_file_alert_description: To process data more accurately, please ensure that the first row of the table is the header, and each row from the second row is a piece of data, and there are no merged cells in the table.

databaseTableRecord.delete_records_confirm: Confirm to delete the selected records?

helpDropdown.about_vectorvein_description:
### Build Your Automated Workflow with the Power of AI
#### Create powerful workflows with drag-and-drop functionality, no programming required.

The open-source version of VectorVein, developed by MakerBi, is available for personal use only and cannot be used for commercial purposes.

typography-paragraph.tip: Can be used to place tips in the interface

uploaderFieldUse.uploader_text: Click or drag file to this area to upload

workflowRunRecordsDrawer.delete_record_warning: Confirm deletion? The record can not be restored after deletion.

agentInvokeDataEdit.tool_name_tip: Can be understood as the function name of the workflow, which can only be numbers, letters, underscores, and hyphens, no more than 64 characters.
agentInvokeDataEdit.tool_name_placeholder: Please enter the tool name, which can only be numbers, letters, underscores, and hyphens.
agentInvokeDataEdit.tool_name_error: Tool name can only be numbers, letters, underscores, and hyphens, no more than 64 characters
agentInvokeDataEdit.tool_description_tip: Used to let AI recognize the function of the tool. The function of the tool should be described as clearly and concisely as possible, especially the input and output.
agentInvokeDataEdit.tool_description_placeholder: Please enter a tool description to let the AI recognize the function of the tool.

codeEditorModal.title: Code editor
codeEditorModal.please_enter_code: Please enter the code, the function name is fixed to main, and the input parameters should be consistent with the set name.

templateEditorModal.title: Template editor
templateEditorModal.format_fields_tip: Quickly use XML tags to format and fill in the template with variable fields

baseNode.ignore_node_tip: After ignoring the node, the node will remain on the canvas, but will not affect the workflow run.

baseField.show_in_use_interface: Whether to display in the use interface

CommentNode.title: Comment node
CommentNode.description: Used to add comments, will not have any effect on the workflow run.

FileLoader.title: Read File
FileLoader.description: Read the contents of the file.

FileUpload.title: Select File
FileUpload.description: Select a local file and get the file path.

TemplateCompose.title: Template compose
TemplateCompose.description: Compose the text according to the template.
TemplateCompose.click_to_add_to_template: Click to add variables to the template
TemplateCompose.name_reserved: template/output is a reserved keyword and cannot be used as a variable name.

TextSplitters.title: Text splitters
TextSplitters.description: Split the text into multiple texts according to the specified method.

TextInOut.title: Simple Input
TextInOut.description: Output the input text as it is. Used when the same text is needed in multiple places.

TextTruncation.title: Text truncation
TextTruncation.description: Truncate the text to the specified length.

TextReplace.title: Text Replace
TextReplace.description: Replace the specified content in the text with other content.
TextReplace.replace_tip: Supports regular expressions (e.g., the regular expression for line breaks is \n). Leave the replacement field empty to delete the text.

RegexExtract.title: Regex Extract
RegexExtract.description: Extract the specified content from the text using a regular expression.
RegexExtract.pattern_tip: Supports regular expressions, extract the content inside the parentheses.
RegexExtract.first_match_tip: Check to extract the first match, the output result is a string, otherwise all matches are extracted, the output result is a list.

OpenAI.title: OpenAI
OpenAI.description: OpenAI's GPT model is a powerful natural language processing AI that understands and generates human language.

ChatGLM.title: ChatGLM
ChatGLM.description: ChatGLM series models, through the injection of code pre-training, supervised fine-tuning and other technologies to align human intentions, with question and answer, multi-round dialogue, code generation and other capabilities.

MiniMax.title: MiniMax
MiniMax.description: MiniMax is an end-to-end multimodal large language model developed by MiniMax.

BaiduWenxin.title: Baidu Wenxin
BaiduWenxin.description: Baidu's new generation of knowledge-enhanced large language model, a new member of the Wenxin large model family, can interact with people, answer questions, assist in creation, and efficiently and conveniently help people obtain information, knowledge and inspiration.

AliyunQwen.title: Qwen
AliyunQwen.description: Qwen is a large-scale pre-training model launched by Alibaba DAMO Academy. The model is based on the Transformer Decoder-only structure and is trained on large-scale global Internet data.

Baichuan.title: Baichuan
Baichuan.description: Baichuan2-53B large model, which integrates intent understanding, information retrieval and reinforcement learning technology, and combines supervised fine-tuning with human intent alignment, has outstanding performance in knowledge Q&A and text creation.

Claude.title: Claude
Claude.description: Claude is a large language model developed by Antropic, trained to give helpful and harmless responses.

Gemini.title: Gemini
Gemini.description: Gemini is Google's latest family of large language models.

Moonshot.title: Moonshot
Moonshot.description: Moonshot is a 100 billion parameter-level large model of "MoonShot AI" company.

Groq.title: Groq
Groq.description: Groq is the AI infrastructure company that delivers fast AI inference.

StableDiffusion.title: Stable Diffusion
StableDiffusion.description: Stable Diffusion is a deep learning text-to-image generation model released in 2022.

DallE.title: DALLÂ·E
DallE.description: OpenAI's most powerful image generation model. It can generate high-quality images with complex details based on the user's recent prompt words.

ImageEditing.title: Image Editing
ImageEditing.description: Used for basic image editing such as cropping, scaling, rotating, etc.
ImageEditing.crop_width_tip: If the crop width is 0, the width is the original image width
ImageEditing.crop_height_tip: If the crop height is 0, the height is the original image height
ImageEditing.scale_width_tip: When set to 0, the height scales proportionally.
ImageEditing.scale_height_tip: When set to 0, the width scales proportionally.
ImageEditing.compress_tip: A compression value of 100 indicates no compression, and the smaller the compression value, the greater the compression ratio.

ImageBackgroundRemoval.title: Image BG Removal
ImageBackgroundRemoval.description: Remove the background of the image to achieve the effect of isolating the main object.

ImageWatermark.title: Image Watermark
ImageWatermark.description: Used for adding watermarks to images.
ImageWatermark.watermark_image_width_ratio_tip: When set to 0, it is automatically calculated according to the watermark image height ratio
ImageWatermark.watermark_image_height_ratio_tip: When set to 0, it is automatically calculated according to the watermark image width ratio

Text.title: Text
Text.description: Used to present text in the user interface.
Text.output_title_tip: Used to distinguish modules in the use interface

Audio.title: Audio
Audio.description: Used to generate audio files, which can realize functions such as text-to-speech and playing audio files.

PictureRender.title: Picture Render
PictureRender.description: Used to render certain content as an image, such as rendering PDF into images.

WorkflowInvokeOutput.title: Workflow invoke output
WorkflowInvokeOutput.description: Used to display the output when called by the workflow invoke node, not displayed in the use interface.

Html.title: HTML
Html.description: Display the page result after HTML rendering.

TextCrawler.title: Text crawler
TextCrawler.description: Used to crawl text from web pages.

BilibiliCrawler.title: Bilibili crawler
BilibiliCrawler.description: Used to crawl videos from Bilibili.

YoutubeCrawler.title: Youtube
YoutubeCrawler.description: Used to crawl videos from youtube.

ButtonTrigger.title: Button trigger
ButtonTrigger.description: Used to trigger workflow runs. As a special node, it can be used without connecting to other nodes.

ScheduleTrigger.title: Scheduled Trigger
ScheduleTrigger.description: Used to trigger workflow runs at specified times.

AddData.title: Add data
AddData.description: Used to add data to the vector database.

DeleteData.title: Delete data
DeleteData.description: Used to delete data from the vector database.

Search.title: Search data
Search.description: Used to search for data in the vector database. The search results are sorted by similarity.

SmartQuery.title: Smart Query
SmartQuery.description: Use natural language to query the database.
SmartQuery.select_all_if_empty: If empty, select all tables in the database. It is recommended to only select the necessary tables for more accurate results.
SmartQuery.use_sample_data_tip: Check this option to provide a table data as a prompt content, which is convenient for AI to refer to the data format. Although it increases the length of the prompt, it can obtain more accurate results.
SmartQuery.include_column_names_tip: When enabled, the output will include column names

GetTableInfo.title: Get Table Information
GetTableInfo.description: Used to obtain information about database tables.
GetTableInfo.select_all_if_empty: If empty, select all tables in the database. It is recommended to only select the necessary tables for more accurate results.
GetTableInfo.output_sql_tip: Output the table structure in CREATE TABLE statement

RunSql.title: Run SQL
RunSql.description: Used to run SQL statements within the user's own database.
RunSql.read_only_tip: When enabled, no modifications will be made to the database tables
RunSql.include_column_names_tip: When enabled, the output will include column names

ProgrammingFunction.title: Programming function
ProgrammingFunction.parameter_name_reserved: language/code/output/use_oversea_node/list_input/error_msg are reserved keywords and cannot be used as parameter names.

ImageSearch.title: Image search
ImageSearch.description: Used to search for images on the Internet.

WorkflowInvoke.title: Workflow invoke
WorkflowInvoke.description: Used to invoke the workflow and get the result.
WorkflowInvoke.fail_all: If this node fails, the entire workflow fails

TextSearch.title: Text Search
TextSearch.description: Used to search for text on the Internet.
TextSearch.combine_result_in_text: Combine search results into a single text

Empty.title: Empty node
Empty.description: Used in cases where it is necessary to ensure that the workflow is executed in order.
Empty.output: Output (does not change the value of the connected node)

Conditional.title: Conditional
Conditional.description: Used to execute different modules according to different conditions.
Conditional.true_output: Output when the condition is met
Conditional.false_output: Output when the condition is not met

RandomChoice.title: Random choice
RandomChoice.description: Used to randomly select an element from a list.

JsonProcess.title: JSON process
JsonProcess.description: Used to process JSON or Python dictionary data.
JsonProcess.default_value: Default value (when Key does not exist)

WorkflowLoop.title: Workflow Loop
WorkflowLoop.description: Used to loop execution of workflows.
WorkflowLoop.fail_all: If this node fails, the entire workflow fails
WorkflowLoop.output_field_cumulative_tip: Accumulate the output results of previous loops, separated by line breaks
WorkflowLoop.output_field_condition_true_output: Output when the condition is met
WorkflowLoop.output_field_condition_false_output: Output when the condition is not met
WorkflowLoop.judgement_end_output_tip: The loop ends when the model outputs this value

GptVision.title: GPT-Vision
GptVision.description: GPT with vision, allowing the model to receive images and answer questions about them.

GlmVision.title: GLM-Vision
GlmVision.description: Realized the deep fusion of visual language features, supporting various image understanding tasks such as visual question answering, image subtitles, visual positioning, and complex object detection.

ClaudeVision.title: Claude-Vision
ClaudeVision.description: Claude 3 series models have new visual capabilities, allowing Claude to understand and analyze images.

GeminiVision.title: Gemini-Vision
GeminiVision.description: Gemini with vision, allowing the model to receive images and answer questions about them.

SpeechRecognition.title: Speech Recognition
SpeechRecognition.description: Used to convert speech to text.

tour.workflow_button_description: Click this button to switch to the workflow interface. Your workflows and official templates can be found here.
tour.database_button_description: Click this button to switch to the database interface. You can create your personal knowledge base here and upload your data for use in workflows.

workspaceLayout.domain_tip: It is recommended that users outside of China use vectorvein.ai.
workspaceLayout.setting_tip1: If you need to use AI-related functions, be sure to configure the relevant information of the large language model in the settings in the upper right corner.
workspaceLayout.setting_tip2: Different workflows/Agents may use different large language models. If you only use certain specific models, it is recommended to check and configure the model you use before running the workflow or using the Agent.

settings.model_id_tip: Model ID is the ID of the model when it is actually deployed. Generally, it is consistent with the model Key, but in cases such as Azure OpenAI and Anthropic on Vertex, the model ID and model Key are inconsistent and need to be set separately.
settings.model_key_tip: Model Key is the unique identifier of the model family, usually consistent with the official identifier.
settings.error_start_shortcut_setting: Failed to set up shortcut key listening
settings.new_chat_with_agent: Start a new chat with Agent
settings.new_chat_with_agent_with_screenshot: Start a new chat with Agent (with screenshot)
settings.recording_using_shorcut_tip: When using a shortcut key to activate the Agent for microphone conversation, it will automatically detect the real-time speaking volume. If it determines that there has been no speech for a short period, it will automatically stop recording.
settings.toggle_recording: Press the shortcut key to start recording for the first time, and press it again to stop recording.
settings.shortcut_conflict: Shortcut conflict, please check and modify (same or included): {key1} and {key2}
settings.asr_openai_setting_same_as_llm: Same as the settings in the Language Models tab
settings.credentials_placeholder: Enter special credentials, such as Google credentials
settings.select_endpoint_tip: After selecting the endpoint, you can configure the specific information of the model under the endpoint, such as the model ID.
settings.delete_model_family_confirm: Are you sure you want to delete {modelFamily} model family?
settings.settings_changed: Settings have changed, please save them.
settings.agent_tool_call_data_generate_model: Agent tool call data generation model
settings.endpoint_model_id_tip: The ID of the model under the current endpoint, leave blank to use the default model ID
settings.save_changes_confirm: You have unsaved changes. Do you want to save them?
